<ns2163:section xmlns:ns2163="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.jndi.introduction.introduction">
    
    <ns2164:title xmlns:ns2164="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JNDI Overview and Architecture</ns2164:title>
    
    <ns2165:para xmlns:ns2165="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        JNDI is implemented as a typical <ns2166:emphasis xmlns:ns2166="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Service Provider</ns2166:emphasis> (SPI) framework. Different
        service providers (that implement the standard interfaces) enable JNDI functionality for
        different types of naming and directory services. These Service Providers may be plugged in, or
        even switched, at runtime.
    </ns2165:para>
    
